# Technical Specification: Integration of Aggregated Cell-Tower Population Density Feed into Resource Model

**Document ID:** MS-ARCH-0192-INT-003  
**Version:** 1.0  
**Author:** Senior Technical Architect, Meridian Systems  
**Date:** October 15, 2024  
**Classification:** TS/SCI (Project-Specific)  
**Approval Status:** Pending Client Review  
**Related Documents:**  
- MS-ARCH-0192-RES-001 (Core Resource Schema)  
- MS-ARCH-0192-OPT-002 (Dispatch Optimizer Module)  

## 1. Overview
This specification outlines the integration of an aggregated cell-tower population density feed into the existing resource model of the FEMA NextGen Emergency Coordination Platform. The feed provides real-time, anonymized population density estimates derived from cellular network tower data, aggregated at a grid level (e.g., 1km x 1km cells) to ensure privacy compliance. This integration enhances the dispatch optimizer by incorporating dynamic population movement data, enabling more accurate ambulance routing and shelter demand estimation during events like Hurricane Milton.

Key constraints:  
- Data usage is restricted to ambulance routing and shelter demand estimation.  
- Feed source: Authorized DHS-partnered cellular data aggregator (e.g., via API from approved vendor like Verizon or AT&T under existing MOUs).  
- Integration scope: Real-time ingestion, no persistent storage of raw data beyond 24-hour rolling windows to minimize data retention risks.  
- Compatibility: Builds on the existing resource schema (v2.1), extending the `ResourceAllocation` and `GeospatialLayer` entities.

This design assumes the platform's current Kubernetes-based microservices architecture and Apache Kafka for event streaming.

## 2. Data Model Updates
The existing resource schema (JSON Schema format) is extended to include population density as a dynamic geospatial layer. No breaking changes; additions are backward-compatible.

### 2.1 Updated Resource Schema (Excerpt)
The core `Resource` entity is augmented with a new `PopulationDensityLayer` reference. Full schema available in MS-ARCH-0192-RES-001.

```json
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "title": "Resource Schema v2.2",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "resourceId": { "type": "string", "description": "Unique identifier (UUID)" },
    "type": { "type": "string", "enum": ["Ambulance", "Shelter", "SupplyDepot"] },
    "status": { "type": "string", "enum": ["Available", "Deployed", "Unavailable"] },
    "location": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "geoPoint": { "type": "string", "description": "GeoJSON Point" },
        "region": { "type": "string", "description": "FEMA Region Code" }
      }
    },
    "allocation": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "optimizerInputs": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "inputType": { "type": "string", "enum": ["Census", "Traffic", "PopulationDensity"] },
              "dataRef": { "type": "string", "description": "Reference to external data layer" }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    // New addition: Population Density Layer
    "populationDensityLayer": {
      "type": "object",
      "description": "Real-time aggregated population density data",
      "properties": {
        "layerId": { "type": "string", "description": "Unique layer identifier (e.g., 'pop-density-milton-2024')" },
        "gridResolution": { "type": "string", "description": "e.g., '1kmx1km'" },
        "timestamp": { "type": "string", "format": "date-time", "description": "Last update time (ISO 8601)" },
        "densityGrid": {
          "type": "array",
          "description": "Array of grid cells with density metrics",
          "items": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "cellId": { "type": "string", "description": "Grid cell identifier (e.g., lat-long hash)" },
              "bounds": { "type": "string", "description": "GeoJSON Polygon for cell boundaries" },
              "densityEstimate": { "type": "number", "description": "Persons per km² (aggregated, anonymized)" },
              "movementTrend": { "type": "string", "enum": ["Increasing", "Decreasing", "Stable"], "description": "Trend over last hour" }
            },
            "required": ["cellId", "bounds", "densityEstimate"]
          }
        },
        "source": { "type": "string", "description": "Data provider (e.g., 'CellTowerAggregatorAPI')" }
      },
      "required": ["layerId", "timestamp", "densityGrid"]
    }
  },
  "required": ["resourceId", "type", "status", "location"]
}
```

### 2.2 Data Flow and Validation
- **Ingestion Validation**: Use JSON Schema validation in the ingestion service to ensure `densityEstimate` values are non-negative floats and `bounds` are valid GeoJSON.
- **Aggregation Level**: Data must be pre-aggregated by the source to prevent PII exposure; platform enforces a minimum grid size of 500m x 500m.
- **TTL**: Density data expires after 24 hours; use Redis for caching with auto-expiry.

## 3. API Contracts
Two new API endpoints are added to the `ResourceService` microservice (RESTful, secured with OAuth 2.0 and mTLS). Existing endpoints remain unchanged.

### 3.1 Ingest Population Density Feed (POST /api/v1/resources/population-density/ingest)
**Description**: Ingests real-time density data from the external feed. Triggered via webhook or polling.

**Request Body** (application/json):
```json
{
  "layerId": "pop-density-milton-2024",
  "timestamp": "2024-10-15T14:30:00Z",
  "densityGrid": [
    {
      "cellId": "grid-27.950-82.457",
      "bounds": "{ \"type\": \"Polygon\", \"coordinates\": [[[27.95, -82.46], [27.96, -82.46], [27.96, -82.45], [27.95, -82.45], [27.95, -82.46]]] }",
      "densityEstimate": 150.5,
      "movementTrend": "Decreasing"
    }
  ],
  "source": "CellTowerAggregatorAPI"
}
```

**Response** (200 OK):
```json
{
  "status": "Ingested",
  "updatedResources": ["resourceId-001", "resourceId-002"]
}
```

