# USAF Joint Logistics Drone Fleet Coordination Algorithm

## Technical Specification — FINAL (v3.2)

**Contract:** FA8802-25-D-0034
**Classification:** SECRET // NOFORN
**Document ID:** MER-JLDA-ALGO-032
**Prepared for:** AFMC Logistics Division, IOC Review Board
**Date:** June 2025

---

## 1. SYSTEM OVERVIEW & DESIGN PHILOSOPHY

The Fleet Coordination Algorithm (FCA) operates as a centralized-planning / decentralized-execution system. A ground-based **Fleet Mission Planner (FMP)** computes globally-optimal mission plans, while each drone's **Onboard Mission Executive (OME)** holds full authority for real-time safety-of-flight decisions including abort, divert, and hold.

**Design Invariants:**
- No drone shall be commanded into a state where a single subsequent failure results in loss of vehicle
- Battery reserve is sacrosanct — the OME will override any FMP directive that violates reserve thresholds
- Manned aircraft always have right-of-way; deconfliction is the drone's burden

---

## 2. DATA MODELS

### 2.1 Core Domain Entities

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ DOMAIN MODEL                                                    │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                                 │
│  Fleet ──1:N──▶ Drone ──1:N──▶ Mission ──1:N──▶ MissionLeg     │
│                   │                                  │          │
│                   ├── BatteryState                    ├── Waypoint│
│                   ├── Position (WGS84)               ├── DropZone│
│                   └── HealthVector                   └── Airspace│
│                                                       Constraint│
│  SupplyRequest ──N:1──▶ DropZone                               │
│  WeatherEnvelope ──1:N──▶ GridCell                             │
│  AirspaceState ──1:N──▶ TrafficTrack                           │
│                                                                 │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

